  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. If caught, potential penalties can include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges:\n- Federal or state criminal charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Substantial prison time (typically 5-20 years)\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties:\n- Significant financial sanctions\n- Asset seizure\n- Forfeitures of laundered funds\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Civil lawsuits\n\nThe specific punishment depends on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Sophistication of the scheme\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific jurisdiction's laws\n\nProsecution is typically handled by federal agencies like the FBI, IRS, or Department of Justice.",
